" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2441_">BookTrust: The UK's largest children's reading charity, BookTrust, runs various programs and events to promote reading among children, including activities and resources for International Children's Book Day.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2443_">The Reading Agency: Another UK-based charity that aims to inspire people to become lifelong readers. It supports ICBD through its reading programs and initiatives in schools and public libraries.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2445_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2446_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2447_">Engaging blog on International Children's Book Day</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2449_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Unleashing Imagination: The Magic of International Children's Book Day<br><br>Once a year, on the 2nd of April, a global event unfolds that has the power to transform, inspire, and unite. International Children's Book Day (ICBD) is not just a celebration; it's a movement. A movement that honours the enchanting world of children's literature and the remarkable influence it holds in shaping young minds, dreams, and futures.<br><br>In the heart of this celebration lies the legacy of Hans Christian Andersen, a storyteller whose fairy tales have transcended time and geography, reminding us of the universal appeal of well-spun tales. But ICBD is more than a tribute to Andersen's genius; it's a call to action—a global plea for the importance of literacy and the joy of reading to be embraced by every child, in every corner of the world.</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="C