-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Wavebreakmedia via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2497_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The celebration of International Children's Book Day is not just a homage to the wonders of children's literature; it is a global acknowledgement of the vital role that reading plays in the development and education of children. It emphasises the power of books to nurture imagination, inspire creativity, and foster an understanding of diverse cultures and worldviews. By bringing children into the fold of reading at an early age, ICBD contributes to the development of informed, empathetic, and curious future generations.<br><br>Books are windows to the world for children. They are tools that help to understand complex emotions, navigate social relationships, and build cognitive skills that are foundational for lifelong learning. Celebrating ICBD underscores the importance of making books accessible to all children, regardless of their background, and highlights the need for inclusive stories that reflect a diversity of experiences and perspectives.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2499_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2500_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2501_">Organisations supporting International Children's Book Day</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/happy-diverse-male-teacher-and-children-with-books-2023-11-27-05-18-47-utc.jpg?v=1708947005" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/happy-diverse-male-teacher-and-children-with-books-2023-11-27-05-18-47-utc.jpg?v=1708947005 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="The Enduring Legacy of Hans Christian Andersen: Inspiration for International Children's Book Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The Enduring Legacy of Hans Christian Andersen: Inspiration for International Children's Book Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2503_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2504_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Wavebreakmedia via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2506_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">A number of organisations worldwide and in the UK play significant roles in raising awareness of International Children's Book Day:</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-2508_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2509_">International Board on Books for Young People (IBBY): The primary organisation behind ICBD, IBBY is an international network committed to bringing books and children together. It advocates for children's literature, supports the production and distribution of quality children's books, and organises activities to celebrate ICBD globally.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2511_">The Children's Book Project: In the UK, this charity works to tackle book poverty and to give every child the opportunity to own their own book. Around ICBD, they organise events and campaigns to highlight the importance of access to books for children.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2513_">BookTrust: The UK's largest children's reading charity, BookTrust, runs various programs and events to promote reading among children, including activities and resources for International Children's Book Day.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2515_">The Reading Agency: Another UK-based charity that aims to inspire people to become lifelong readers. It supports ICBD through its reading programs and initiatives in schools and public libraries.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2517_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2518_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2519_">Engaging blog on International Children's Book Day</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/studio-shot-of-a-group-of-kids-sitting-on-chairs-a-2023-11-27-04-49-06-utc.jpg?v=1708947140" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/studio-shot-of-a-group-of-kids-sitting-on-chairs-a-2023-11-27-04-49-06-utc.jpg?v=1708947140 1536w" width="1000" height="657" alt="Fostering a Love for Reading: The Importance of Children's Literature in Today's World - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Fostering a Love for Reading: The Importance of Children's Literature in Today's World - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2521_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2522_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by YuriArcursPeopleimages via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2524_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Unleashing Imagination: The Magic of International Children's Book Day<br><br>Once a year, on the 2nd of April, a global event unfolds that has the power to transform, inspire, and unite. International Children's Book Day (ICBD) is not just a celebration; it's a movement. A movement that honours the enchanting world of children's literature and the remarkable influence it holds in shaping young minds, dreams, and futures.<br><br>In the heart of this celebration lies the legacy of Hans Christian Andersen, a storyteller whose fairy tales have transcended time and geography, reminding us of the universal appeal of well-spun tales. But ICBD is more than a tribute to Andersen's genius; it's a call to action—a global plea for the importance of literacy and the joy of reading to be embraced by every child, in every corner of the world.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2526_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2527_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2528_">Why celebrate ICBD?</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/book-day-holiday-card-on-wooden-table-top-2023-11-27-05-10-53-utc.jpg?v=1708947384" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/book-day-holiday-card-on-wooden-table-top-2023-11-27-05-10-53-utc.jpg?v=1708947384 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Reading Without Borders: Promoting Children's Literacy on International Children's Book Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Reading Without Borders: Promoting Children's Literacy on International Children's Book Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2530_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2531_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Beo88 via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2533_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Imagine a world where every child has access to a treasure trove of stories, where every book opens a door to new adventures, lessons, and discoveries. This is the vision of International Children's Book Day. It's a day that recognises the critical role of reading in child development - cultivating imagination, empathy, and understanding. It's a reminder that in the hustle of our digital age, the simple act of reading a book can be the most revolutionary activity a child engages in.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2535_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2536_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2537_">The champions behind the cause</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/three-children-of-students-with-books-preparation-2023-11-27-05-34-29-utc.jpg?v=1708947503" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/three-children-of-students-with-books-preparation-2023-11-27-05-34-29-utc.jpg?v=1708947503 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="IBBY's Role in Enriching International Children's Book Day Celebrations - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="IBBY's Role in Enriching International Children's Book Day Celebrations - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2539_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2540_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by OlhaRomaniuk via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2542_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Organisations like the International Board on Books for Young People (IBBY), The Children's Book Project, BookTrust, and The Reading Agency stand at the forefront of this noble cause. These champions of children's literature work tirelessly not only to celebrate ICBD but to ensure that every day is an opportunity for a child to discover the joy of reading. They advocate for inclusivity, accessibility, and the importance of nurturing a diverse literary landscape where every child can see themselves reflected in the pages of a book.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2544_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2545_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2546_">Signposting for support</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/happy-schoolteacher-and-students-happening-a-good-2023-11-27-05-12-44-utc.jpg?v=1708947594" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/happy-schoolteacher-and-students-happening-a-good-2023-11-27-05-12-44-utc.jpg?v=1708947594 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="From Page to Imagination: Celebrating Diversity in Children's Books - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="From Page to Imagination: Celebrating Diversity in Children's Books - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2548_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2549_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Wavebreakmedia via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2551_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To learn more, get involved, or support the cause, consider reaching out to the organisations mentioned above. Each plays a vital role in making books accessible to children and advocating for the importance of children's literature. Your support can help ensure that the magic of reading reaches every child, not just on International Children's Book Day, but every day.<br><br>In celebrating ICBD, we celebrate the potential of every child to become a lifelong learner, a dreamer, and a doer. Let's turn the page together on a future where every child can discover the joy and the power of a good book.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9e75" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-uojGG hMqLeX pf-2714_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-ilfuhL bpQaoh"><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2694_ pf-r